          "scid": "thig2.7:1.0.3",
          "en": "7. Mittā"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig2.7:1.0.4",
          "en": "“On full-moon day and on the fifteenth day, And eke the eighth of either half the month, I kept the feast; I kept the precepts eight, The extra fasts, enamoured of the gods, And fain to dwell in homes celestial."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig2.7:1.0.5",
          "en": "To-day one meal, head shaved, a yellow robe— Enough for me. I want no heaven of gods. Heart’s pain, heart’s pining, have I trained away.”"
        }
      ],
